- VSCode Version: 1.5.3
- OS Version: Windows

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Add a settings with a description that contains `\n`:

   ``` json
   "configuration": {
       "title": "Test config",
       "properties": {
           "test.test": {
               "description": "\nnewline"
           }
       }
   }
   ```
2. Open the Default Settings page:

   ![](http://i.imgur.com/sZX2ab6.png)

Possible solutions:
- strip `\n` from descriptions
- add `\t//` before each `\n` character

- VSCode Version: 1.5.3
- OS Version: OS X 10.10.3

Intermittently I keep receiving "only absolute urls are supported". Sometimes, the command execution works and sometimes it can't even find a command. If it finds a command then execution intermittently keeps displaying this error. 

Any thoughts? Below is the code snippet where debugger throws exception (index.js line 54).

```
// build request object
        var options = new Request(url, opts);

        if (!options.protocol || !options.hostname) {
            throw new Error('only absolute urls are supported');
        }
```
